This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image restoration tasks. The use of supervised learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the incorporation of a supervised regularization term suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of convolutional sparse coding suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
